# OSI Model

## 📌 Overview
The Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) Model is a conceptual framework used to understand how data travels between devices over a network.

---

## 🎯 Why OSI Model?

- Standardizes network communication
- Helps troubleshoot network issues
- Separates networking into layers
- Makes protocol development easier

---

## 🏗 The 7 Layers

| Layer | Name | Example |
|-------|------|---------|
| 7 | Application | HTTP, FTP |
| 6 | Presentation | SSL, JPEG |
| 5 | Session | NetBIOS |
| 4 | Transport | TCP, UDP |
| 3 | Network | IP |
| 2 | Data Link | Ethernet |
| 1 | Physical | Cable, Fiber |

---

## 📡 Devices

Layer 1 → Hub

Layer 2 → Switch

Layer 3 → Router

---

## 🌍 Real World Example

Sending a WhatsApp message:

Application → Creates the message

Transport → Breaks into segments

Network → Finds destination

Data Link → Frames

Physical → Sends bits

